      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A plain <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.54</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.25</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.55</measure>),  complete above and broken below. The right side was hollowed out, to create a recessed panel.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p> The text is on the lower edge of a gameboard (type 3Rows.4, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.43</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.97</measure>, carefully cut, circles <measure dim="diameter" type="length">0.03</measure>, central <rs type="decoration">rosette</rs>s in circle <measure dim="diameter" type="length">0.10</measure>), within the recessed panel on the right side; the text is cut level with the top of a second text (not yet published) on the adjacent side.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p> Irregular letters, ave <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.03</measure>; scroll and letter above line for abbreviations.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0468" notAfter="0600">Late fifth/sixth century</date> (<rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
 		<div type="textpart_section"><ab>
		<lb n="1"/><g type="cross"/> <g type="cross"/> <w lemma="ἐπί">ἐπὶ</w> <persName key="photius1" reg="Φλάβιος Φώτιος" full="yes" type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Φλάβιος"><expan><abbr>Φλ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αβίου</supplied></expan></name> <name reg="Φώτιος">Φωτίου</name></persName> <w lemma="σχολαστικός"><rs type="profession" key="scholasticus"><expan><abbr>σχο</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">λαστικοῦ</supplied></expan></rs></w> <w lemma="καί"><expan><abbr>κ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">αὶ</supplied></expan></w> <w lemma="πατήρ"><rs type="official-secul" key="pater"><expan><abbr>πατρ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ός</supplied></expan></rs></w> <g type="cross"/>
		</ab></div>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
		<ab>
		Under Flavius Photios, <term lang="la">scholasticus</term> and <term lang="la">pater</term></ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>ii. This is the third of the gameboards given by Flavius Photios; see <xref type="inscription" n="68" href="050010">5.10</xref>, <xref type="inscription" n="69" href="050014">5.14</xref> and discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="V.44">V.44</xref> and <xref type="eAla-text" n="V.47">V.47</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList" key="HadrBath">Hadrianic Baths</rs>: during clearing in the Aleipterion</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation"><rs type="monuList" key="HadrBath" cert="low">Hadrianic Baths</rs></rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Museum</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

